{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FR1b8q2CvoKJNWVdRKTjnA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t- [qwerty81 in-flight fixes — DONE](project_qwerty81_in_flight_fixes.md) — archive marker. All 9 reconstruction commits landed on main 2026-04-26. Outstanding follow-ups: launcher `--max-chain` + idle-restart guard.\n2\t- [Recovery plan: reset-disaster 2026-04-26 — DONE](project_recovery_after_reset_disaster_2026-04-26.md) — Phase B + Phase A reconstruction shipped. Durable rules: commit-before-launch + global destructive-git ban (now in GLOBAL_RULES.md, commit 527162a).\n3\t- [qwerty81 karma observability](project_qwerty81_karma_observability.md) — 2026-04-26 16:20 EDT: karma 75, 25 cmts, 18 verdicts, **est_final 102.49 (rank 16/37)**. CR's +14 lead at identical karma+qrm = (a) timing artifact: our latest 7 cmts still `in_review` (will mechanically catch up); (b) cadence: CR posts steady 2.3/h × 11h, we post in bursts with 16h+ idle gaps. Length is NOT the bottleneck — we already write 2683 vs CR's 2228 chars. Activate qwerty82/83.\n4\t- [Leaderboard / competitor strategy analysis — DONE](project_followup_leaderboard_analysis.md) — top of leaderboard is multiple 3-agent owners (not one team). Old regression `est_final ≈ 0.92·karma + 1.29·qrm` is R²=0.45; richer 5-feature reaches only R²=0.59 — **the hidden factor is recency-trajectory / cadence**, not on the leaderboard. Citation tactics A/B/C/D extracted from this. Re-run via `read-koala-leaderboard` skill.\n5\t- [Three-agent competition plan](project_three_agent_plan.md) — qwerty81 (Opus, biased, live, 25 cmts/18 verdicts), qwerty82 (Sonnet, biased, NEXT-SESSION KICKOFF — full procedure in §qwerty82 fork procedure), qwerty83 (Sonnet, unbiased, after 82). STRICT RULE: byte-identical forks, single-variable changes only. Competition ends Thursday 2026-04-30.\n6\t- [qwerty81 timing strategy](project_qwerty81_timing_strategy.md) — competitor diurnal pattern (13× swing; dead zone 13–17 UTC = 09–13 EDT) + qwerty81's lag (29.3h vs FR's 33.5h, 14/18 papers in cite pool) + decision recipe for \"is now a good time to launch?\" Recurring user lookup.\n7\t- [Scope: dev-time token economy ONLY (not agent execution)](feedback_scope_economy.md) — narrow scope for *this* Claude Code session's edits; competition agents run at full intended cost. Misapplied 2026-04-26.\n8\t- [Subagent summaries are unreliable on this stack](feedback_subagent_summaries_unreliable.md) — verify spec-implementation subagents via git diff, not their summary; they describe narrative not output. Hit twice 2026-04-25 with general-purpose / sonnet.\n9\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a859316b-e0dd-4a49-a8cd-481edb4652d0","uuid":"cfc4e3f4-7937-4c5a-84e0-93c0c42cfb57","timestamp":"2026-04-26T20:42:00.991Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/.claude/projects/-home-mila-s-stephane-gazaille-qwerty81/memory/MEMORY.md","content":"- [qwerty81 in-flight fixes — DONE](project_qwerty81_in_flight_fixes.md) — archive marker. All 9 reconstruction commits landed on main 2026-04-26. Outstanding follow-ups: launcher `--max-chain` + idle-restart guard.\n- [Recovery plan: reset-disaster 2026-04-26 — DONE](project_recovery_after_reset_disaster_2026-04-26.md) — Phase B + Phase A reconstruction shipped. Durable rules: commit-before-launch + global destructive-git ban (now in GLOBAL_RULES.md, commit 527162a).\n- [qwerty81 karma observability](project_qwerty81_karma_observability.md) — 2026-04-26 16:20 EDT: karma 75, 25 cmts, 18 verdicts, **est_final 102.49 (rank 16/37)**. CR's +14 lead at identical karma+qrm = (a) timing artifact: our latest 7 cmts still `in_review` (will mechanically catch up); (b) cadence: CR posts steady 2.3/h × 11h, we post in bursts with 16h+ idle gaps. Length is NOT the bottleneck — we already write 2683 vs CR's 2228 chars. Activate qwerty82/83.\n- [Leaderboard / competitor strategy analysis — DONE](project_followup_leaderboard_analysis.md) — top of leaderboard is multiple 3-agent owners (not one team). Old regression `est_final ≈ 0.92·karma + 1.29·qrm` is R²=0.45; richer 5-feature reaches only R²=0.59 — **the hidden factor is recency-trajectory / cadence**, not on the leaderboard. Citation tactics A/B/C/D extracted from this. Re-run via `read-koala-leaderboard` skill.\n- [Three-agent competition plan](project_three_agent_plan.md) — qwerty81 (Opus, biased, live, 25 cmts/18 verdicts), qwerty82 (Sonnet, biased, NEXT-SESSION KICKOFF — full procedure in §qwerty82 fork procedure), qwerty83 (Sonnet, unbiased, after 82). STRICT RULE: byte-identical forks, single-variable changes only. Competition ends Thursday 2026-04-30.\n- [qwerty81 timing strategy](project_qwerty81_timing_strategy.md) — competitor diurnal pattern (13× swing; dead zone 13–17 UTC = 09–13 EDT) + qwerty81's lag (29.3h vs FR's 33.5h, 14/18 papers in cite pool) + decision recipe for \"is now a good time to launch?\" Recurring user lookup.\n- [Scope: dev-time token economy ONLY (not agent execution)](feedback_scope_economy.md) — narrow scope for *this* Claude Code session's edits; competition agents run at full intended cost. Misapplied 2026-04-26.\n- [Subagent summaries are unreliable on this stack](feedback_subagent_summaries_unreliable.md) — verify spec-implementation subagents via git diff, not their summary; they describe narrative not output. Hit twice 2026-04-25 with general-purpose / sonnet.\n","numLines":9,"startLine":1,"totalLines":9}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_012hAcAKtKacpGncgGCMj6r2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CFLMJxtSByK3pYiMwuTk1q","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/.claude/projects/-home-mila-s-stephane-gazaille-qwerty81/memory/project_qwerty81_fresh_batch_deadlock.md","content":"---\nname: qwerty81 fresh-batch eligibility deadlock\ndescription: When the platform releases a fresh paper batch and the entire visible in_review feed is <1h old, the ≥2 other-owner-commenter gate rejects everything; session ends idle at peak hours\ntype: project\n---\n\nObserved 2026-04-26 ~20:40 UTC (16:40 EDT, peak hours, NOT in 13–17 UTC dead zone).\n\n`get_papers(limit=100)` returned 100 papers, all `in_review`, all `created_at` ~0.7h ago — a single mass release. Comment counts: 0 on 95, 1 on 5. Yesterday's batch had already transitioned to deliberating/reviewed and was no longer in the in_review feed.\n\nThe selection rule in `agent_configs/qwerty81/CLAUDE.md` requires \"≥2 distinct other-owner commenters\" as a HARD gate. Zero papers passed. Session-loop stop rule fired (\"no qualifying papers remain\") → ended idle.\n\n**Why:** the gate's documented justification (\"doesn't reject fresh-batch candidates that are still accumulating commenters\") assumes papers in the feed have had hours to accumulate. When a batch drops mass-synchronously, the gate creates a deadlock for first-movers — exactly the agents who get cited later under the citation rule \"Credit the first proposer.\" Skipping at peak hours is the worst possible cadence outcome (hidden est_final factor per `project_followup_leaderboard_analysis.md`).\n\n**How to apply:**\n- Before the user's next CLAUDE.md edit, surface this trade-off: either lower the gate to ≥1 (or 0) for papers <2h old, OR add an explicit \"fresh-batch override\" branch that picks 3 highest-trending-domain papers regardless of comment count.\n- For now (without rule change), the session correctly ended per current rules; do not silently override the hard gate mid-session.\n- This deadlock will repeat every ~24h while the platform releases papers in mass batches. If observed again, log the timestamp here so we can characterize the release schedule.\n\n**Adjacent observation:** `get_notifications(unread_only=false)` returns 500. Only `unread_only=true` works. If we need historical notifications (e.g. to check past PAPER_DELIBERATING events), that route is currently broken.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1262,"cache_read_input_tokens":71046,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1262,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":69,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a859316b-e0dd-4a49-a8cd-481edb4652d0","uuid":"a481eec2-520e-4e08-a6aa-2b0fa40af594"}
